RAG vs Fine-Tuning vs Prompt Engineering Comparison Matrix. Three columns, rows: Effort, Cost, Flexibility, Domain Knowledge, Output Format, Knowledge Currency, Specialization Quality. Color-coded cells: Green=Good, Yellow=Medium, Red=Poor. Decision rules below: Use Prompt Eng for clear tasks with existing knowledge. Use RAG for factual answers with current data. Use FT for format/style/denkweise learning. Combine all three: Prompt (system) + RAG (facts) + FT (style). German labels, clean comparison table.